Hits all the notes of a great bourbon barrel aged imperial stout. Oak, vanilla, cocoa, coffee, roasted malts, get some coconut, all enhanced by the bourbon. Medium to full mouthfeel. Great beer, highly recommend!

Aroma is deep roasted coffee, malts, and dark semi-sweet chocolate. Appearance is pitch black with a dark brown head, beautiful. Taste follows the nose to a T. Amazingly well-done brew from Brew Dogs. Highly recommend.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Another beer in Ommegang's Game of Disappointment series... Bottles just gather dust on the stores of the local stores, no one who has tried these would ever think of going back for more. Shocking Ommegang could fail this hard. Unless you want way over-carbonated, massive clove-banana, Belgian yeast slaps in the face, regardless of style and characteristics they claim to be going for, stay away. At this point I just buy one, pour the beer down the sink and put the bottle in my collection...

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #3 - Fire and Blood

review_blob:
Maybe the best beer I've ever tasted. Great quality coffee, dark chocolate, vanilla, and just the perfect amount of chilies! Was expecting a sweeter beer, at 13%, but was shocked and happy it wasn't! Amazing beer from this collaboration! 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Decent IPA I guess, but I've had two bottles and never even got a hint of coconut in the aroma or taste in either one. Tried at all temperature ranges and nothing helped. Since there is no coconut, Stone makes other IPAs that are better, so I won't be going back to this one.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Deserves all the hype! This beer is amazing. One of, if not, the best tasting beer I've ever tried. Almost complete perfection, the only thing I could even consider dinging it for is it is a little thinner than I'd like (and by just a hair), but that's not to say that this beer could be much better. World class for sure!

Malt bomb! The smell is malts, caramel, molasses, and a little nuttiness. Taste is amazing. Tastes of maple, caramel, raisins, malts, oak, and no taste of alcohol, but does give a nice warming sensation going down. Another amazing offering from Founders.

Batch from 12/12 from a bomber. This beer disappointed me greatly. The only thing I can taste is the alcohol. Kind of a whiskey/rum flavor. Looks fairly normal, but smell and taste is dominated by the booze. Very hard to pull out any other characteristics. Many other stouts I'd choose over this one.

review_blob:
Thought I should avoid this one, but I am up for trying anything once. Probably should've stuck with my initial thought. Smell is of small hint of fig, cherry, and caramel, but alcohol is the dominate aroma. Taste mirrors almost exactly. Boozy and not much else to save this beer. I even tried aging it a year before trying... Do not recommend.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Cascara Quad

review_blob:
Another amazing IPA created under Stone's sphere of influence! Grapefruit is the most prominent feature in the nose and taste, which it should be being called Grapefruit Slam. The 8.2% ABV is hidden masterfully. No taste of alcohol and little to no alcohol warming on the way down. Very refreshing and very well done. Highly recommend to all hopheads!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Stone Stochasticity Project Grapefruit Slam IPA

review_blob:
This beer surpassed all my expectations. Aroma is pineapple and a touch of roasted jalapeos, which from the ingredients and deScription leads you to expect. Flavor follows the nose. Amazing pineapple flavor in which the sweetness is cut by the roasted jalapeo follow by a little pepper heat warming. Amazing beer, recommend highly. This brewery is going places!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not a fan of Scoth Ale/Wee Heavies usually, but this beer is amazing! This may be one of my top 5 beers I've ever had. The amazingly complex bourbonesque-scotch greatness leaves the most awesome lingering taste in your mouth. Must try for any beer lover!
